70.2	Isaiah	Isaiah	Isaiah ( or ; Hebrew: , Modern Tiberian ; Greek: , Ēsaïās ; "Yahu is salvation") was a prophet who lived in the 8th-century BC Kingdom of Judah. Jews and Christians consider the Book of Isaiah a part of their Biblical canon; he is the first listed (although not the earliest) of the neviim akharonim, the latter prophets. Many of the New Testament teachings of Jesus refer to the book of Isaiah.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/50/Isaiah_%28Bible_Card%29.jpg/250px-Isaiah_%28Bible_Card%29.jpg
